    <title>Laravel Roles Permissions</title>
    <link>https://kienngd.98t1.net/laravel_roles_permissions/</link>
    <pubDate>Fri, 27 Nov 2020 09:44:04 &#43;0700</pubDate><author>
        <name>Kien Nguyen</name>
    </author><guid>https://kienngd.98t1.net/laravel_roles_permissions/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>Create role, permission</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span><span class="lnt">2
</span><span class="lnt">3
</span><span class="lnt">4
</span><span class="lnt">5
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-php" data-lang="php"><span class="k">use</span> <span class="nx">Spatie\Permission\Models\Role</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="k">use</span> <span class="nx">Spatie\Permission\Models\Permission</span><span class="p">;</span>

<span class="nv">$role</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">Role</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="na">create</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;name&#39;</span> <span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="s1">&#39;admin&#39;</span><span class="p">]);</span>
<span class="nv">$permission</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">Permission</span><span class="o">::</span><span class="na">create</span><span class="p">([</span><span class="s1">&#39;name&#39;</span> <span class="o">=&gt;</span> <span class="s1">&#39;create-articles&#39;</span><span class="p">]);</span>
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p><strong>Assign / Sync / Revoke permission to role</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt"> 1
</span><span class="lnt"> 2
</span><span class="lnt"> 3
</span><span class="lnt"> 4
</span><span class="lnt"> 5
</span><span class="lnt"> 6
</span><span class="lnt"> 7
</span><span class="lnt"> 8
</span><span class="lnt"> 9
</span><span class="lnt">10
</span><span class="lnt">11
</span><span class="lnt">12
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-php" data-lang="php"><span class="c1">// Assign
</span><span class="c1"></span><span class="nv">$role</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">givePermissionTo</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$permission</span><span class="p">);</span> <span class="c1">// $permission can be string / object / array of strings / array of objects
</span><span class="c1"></span><span class="nv">$permission</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">assignRole</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$role</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="c1">// Sync
</span><span class="c1"></span><span class="nv">$role</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">syncPermissions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$permissions</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nv">$permission</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">syncRoles</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$roles</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="c1">// Revoke
</span><span class="c1"></span><span class="nv">$role</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">revokePermissionTo</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$permission</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nv">$permission</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">removeRole</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$role</span><span class="p">);</span>

</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p><strong>Check roles permissons</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span><span class="lnt">2
</span><span class="lnt">3
</span><span class="lnt">4
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-php" data-lang="php"><span class="nv">$role</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">hasPermissionTo</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$permission</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nv">$role</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">hasAnyPermission</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$permissions</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nv">$role</span><span class="o">-&gt;</span><span class="na">hasAllPermissions</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="nv">$permissions</span><span class="p">);</span>

</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div>]]></description>
</item><item>
    <title>Apiato laravel based framework</title>
    <link>https://kienngd.98t1.net/apiato/</link>
    <pubDate>Thu, 26 Nov 2020 08:36:20 &#43;0700</pubDate><author>
        <name>Kien Nguyen</name>
    </author><guid>https://kienngd.98t1.net/apiato/</guid>
    <description><![CDATA[<p>Home page: <a href="http://docs.apiato.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">http://docs.apiato.io/</a></p>
<p><strong>Create project using composer from latest stable</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">composer create-project apiato/apiato apiato9
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p>Then edit the .env file.</p>
<p><strong>Migrate database</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">php artisan migrate
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p><strong>Create admin user, some permissions, roles</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">php artisan db:seed
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p>Default account is: <a href="mailto:admin@admin.com" rel="">admin@admin.com</a> / admin.</p>
<p><strong>Add all current permissions to admin role.</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">php artisan apiato:permissions:toRole admin
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p><strong>Install OAuth 2.0</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">php artisan passport:install
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p>Then edit file <strong>.env</strong> update CLIENT_WEB_ADMIN_ID, CLIENT_WEB_ADMIN_SECRET with the new created value.</p>
<p><strong>Install ApiDocJs</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">yarn install
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p><strong>Create api doc</strong></p>
<div class="highlight"><div class="chroma">
<table class="lntable"><tr><td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code><span class="lnt">1
</span></code></pre></td>
<td class="lntd">
<pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">php artisan apiato:apidoc
</code></pre></td></tr></table>
</div>
</div><p>Your default document url is: http://<Your domain>/api/documentation and http://<Your domain>/api/private/documentation</p>
<p>Default result is saved in: <strong>public/api/documentation/</strong></p>]]></description>
</item><item>
